{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1781683030,"nonce":"M8+2a32zZbFLHnQvZYwXW77PdhQ=","title":"Window functions (OVER / PARTITION BY)","message":"No window-function support: ROW_NUMBER/RANK/DENSE_RANK/LAG/LEAD, aggregate-as-window (SUM(...) OVER (...)), with PARTITION BY and ORDER BY in the window, and frame clauses (ROWS/RANGE BETWEEN).\n\nDepends on the aggregate-expression work (the aggregates bug) since window aggregates reuse the same aggregate constructors with an OVER clause. Lower priority than aggregation/predicates/upsert but commonly needed for ranking and running-total queries. Postgres-first.","files":null}]}